To run your project smoothly without running into the "Port already in use" or "PowerShell Execution Policy" errors, here is the exact sequence of commands you should use. 

Open a new terminal in your project root (`Interview TA Bot`), and run the following:

#kill process
taskkill /IM node.exe /F
taskkill /IM python.exe /F
taskkill /IM electron.exe /F

# cd to desktop app
cd desktop-app

#kill process
taskkill /IM node.exe /F
taskkill /IM python.exe /F
taskkill /IM electron.exe /F
npm.cmd run desktop


**1. Navigate to the desktop-app folder:**
```powershell
cd desktop-app
```

**2. Clean up any stale background processes (Optional but recommended):**
If the app crashed previously or was closed improperly, it might leave Node or Python running in the background. Running these commands will kill them so you don't get a "Port 5173/8000 is already in use" error.
```powershell
taskkill /IM node.exe /F
taskkill /IM python.exe /F
taskkill /IM electron.exe /F
```
*(Note: It's completely fine if it says "process not found" for any of these, it just means they weren't running.)*

**3. Start the application:**
Use `npm.cmd` instead of just `npm`. This bypasses the PowerShell security error (`npm.ps1 cannot be loaded because running scripts is disabled`) that you might see on Windows.
```powershell
npm.cmd run desktop
```

This single command will spin up your Vite development server and automatically launch the Electron window along with your Python backend!